e a solution.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating native image and reflection**\\n\\nI need to think about how to create a native image that requires reflection on internal JDK types. I can implement Type interfaces as test helper classes and use reflection on the FieldSerializerGenericsUtil. The rule states that test class or file names shouldn’t include a dollar sign, which is fine since I’m considering a top-level public class. However, invoking package-private methods might create issues since I'll need to set accessibility to access library internals and metadata. Reflection could be necessary here.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring custom Type implementations**\\n\\nI'm diving into the details of creating custom Type implementations. I need a ParameterizedType with the raw type List.class, and the actual type arguments should include a new GenericArrayType with String.class as the component type. I'm asking myself if the interface allows for this—good news! It does, as it returns the Type correctly. It seems like the library branch is going to accept this solution. Let's see how it all ties together!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_FecntUolvCXB7SBhCeLOd29q|fc_0e4848015b2dc38a0169f28c1f07e8819184f6367dbef568b8", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg \"pushGenericsScope|popGenericsScope|getGenericsScope\" -n /home/jovan/Work/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/com.esotericsoftware/kryo-shaded/3.0.3/main/extracted/com/esotericsoftware/kryo/Kryo.java /home/jovan/Work/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/com.esotericsoftware/kryo-shaded/3.0.3/main/extracted/com/esotericsoftware/kryo/Generics.java", "timeout": 10}, "partialJson": "{\"command\":\"rg \\\"pushGenericsScope|popGenericsScope|getGenericsScope\\\" -n /home/jovan/Work/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/com.esotericsoftware/kryo-shaded/3.0.3/main/extracted